Package: packetnet-headend
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Tom Fanning <tom@m0lte.uk>
Depends: systemd
Section: hamradio
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/packet-net/packet.net
Description: packet.net split-station RF head-end daemon
 A small, static, headless Go daemon for a box (typically a Raspberry Pi) that
 physically holds the NinoTNC modems and Tait radio-control cables. It exposes
 every attached serial device as a raw TCP byte pipe, plus a tiny machine API
 (inventory + line-control) and an mDNS advertisement, so a remote Packet.NET
 node (pdn) can discover the fleet, dial the pipes, and drive the devices with
 its own drivers. It does no device identification and no protocol parsing —
 a dumb, transparent multiplexer. Auth-less by design: runs on a trusted LAN or
 Tailscale tailnet. Single static binary, no runtime or library dependencies.
